OL,3,CCan Reeves increase investment and
OL,4,Cavoid austerity?
OL,6,FHowever, the amount she can sensibly
OL,7,Fborrow is constrained by her other
OL,8,Ffiscal rule, namely to finance all day-
OL,9,Fto-day public spending - on public
OL,10,Fsector wages, welfare payments and so
OL,11,Fon - with taxation by some future date
OL,12,Fthat has not yet been specified (and
OL,13,Fwill be in the budget). In other
OL,14,Fwords, she will not borrow to pay the
OL,15,Fgovernment's running costs.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/13
