OL,3,CCan Reeves increase investment and
OL,4,Cavoid austerity?
OL,6,FSuch an investment-fueled increase in
OL,7,FGDP is not to be sniffed at. But it
OL,8,Fdoes not remotely make the increase in
OL,9,Fgovernment capital spending self-
OL,10,Ffinancing before the next general
OL,11,Felection.
OL,13,FOr to put it another way, if this
OL,14,Fgovernment wants to achieve its twin
OL,15,Fambitions of increasing investment and
OL,16,Favoiding austerity in public services,
OL,17,Ftaxes have to go up, quite
OL,18,Fsignificantly - perhaps by as much as
OL,19,Fan eye-watering #25bn per annum,
OL,20,Faccording to the Institute of Fiscal
OL,21,FStudies.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
