OL,3,CCan Reeves increase investment and
OL,4,Cavoid austerity?
OL,6,FAnd the tragedy for this government is
OL,7,Fthat it was partly avoidable. The
OL,8,Fdilemma would have been less acute if
OL,9,Fshe hadn't tied her hands during the
OL,10,Fgeneral election campaign by promising
OL,11,Fnot to raise the rates of income tax,
OL,12,Fcorporation tax and VAT.
OL,14,FSo much of what has so far gone wrong
OL,15,Ffor Starmer and Reeves is that they
OL,16,Fdidn't think enough about the
OL,17,Fimplications for their ability to
OL,18,Fgovern of what they thought they
OL,19,Fneeded to promise voters in order to
OL,20,Fget into government.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/13
