OL,3,CCan Reeves increase investment and
OL,4,Cavoid austerity?
OL,6,FUnlike Blair and Brown in 1997, they
OL,7,Fdid too little detailed preparation
OL,8,Ffor the heavy burdens of being in
OL,9,Foffice.
OL,11,FReeves may find a happy compromise
OL,12,Fthat somehow reconciles short-term
OL,13,Fpublic service rehabilitation with
OL,14,Flong-term growth. But my goodness it
OL,15,Fwill be hard.
